## Introduction

NetLogo 7 introduces a new, more powerful way of selecting colors, which
replaces Color Swatches. As was the case previously there are four
different contexts in which colors can be selected: from the Tools menu,
from a Color Input widget, when selecting a plot pen color and when
editing a Note. The ways in which the versions differ involve whether a
selected color can be copied or "picked," whether transparency is
allowed, and what forms of input and output specifications are allowed,
as will be described later.

## Colors in NetLogo

For information on the different ways colors are represented in NetLogo
see the
[Colors](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/programming.html#colors)
section of the NetLogo Programming Guide. The NetLogo primitives for
working with colors are
[approximate-hsb](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#approximate-hsb) [approximate-rgb](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#approximate-rgb) [base-colors](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#base-colors) [color](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#color) [extract-hsb](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#extract-hsb) [extract-rgb](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#extract-rgb) [hsb](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#hsb) [import-pcolors](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#import-pcolors) [import-pcolors-rgb](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#import-pcolors-rgb) [pcolor](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#pcolor) [rgb](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#rgb) [scale-color](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#scale-color) [shade-of?](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#shade-of) [wrap-color](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/dictionary.html#wrap-color).
The [Palette
Extension](https://ccl.northwestern.edu/netlogo/docs/palette.html)
offers additional ways to work with colors.

All versions of the Color Picker have two tabs, Simple, and Advanced.
The Simple tab allows users to pick a color from a rectangular grid.
This is analogous to the Color Swatches dialog, although it is more
visually streamlined.

